         <abstract>
            <p>The minimum root separation of an arbitrary polynomial $P$ is defined as the minimum of the distances between distinct (real or complex) roots of $P$. Some asymptotically good lower bounds for the root separation of $P$ are given, where $P$ may have multiple zeros. There are applications in the analysis of complexity of algorithms and in the theory of algebraic and transcendental numbers.</p>
